# Git commits

When creating git commits in this repository:

- Never pass `--trailer "Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>"` or any Cursor co-author trailer.
- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` lines to commit messages.
- Use `git commit-tree` (after `git add` + `git write-tree`) instead of `git commit` if the environment injects co-author trailers automatically.
- Keep commit messages focused on the change; do not mention Cursor in messages.
